from soh kam yung subject re protection of serial line martin john gregory mgregory write i start to look at some device do serial datum transmission over fairly decent distance in fairly noisy environment and have see a variety of scheme for protect the transceiver and the rest of the circuit from transient on the serial line i leave wonder what be the best way of do thi how necessary be it stuff delete what be the wisdom on thi out there tum martin from what i know protection be necessary esp if you plan to route the cable into an unknown environment out of ymy control thing like accidental short between the signal line and power cable or even lightning strike be very likely and i do think you like to see the sight of ymy computer go up in smoke even ethernet card be protect i look at the one in my pc and the connector be protect by a ga discharge tube but if you plan to use the serial cable for internal rout in control environment it should be reasonably safe not to have them suggestion look in the rs datum book they have several transceiver that have overvoltage protection among them include the and and the maxim be suppose to be electrically isolate one but still need opto-isolator to work do ask me why i never use them before another alternative be an surge protector two be list in the rs catalogue if you need additional info stock no just e-mail me soh kam yung 